hello I'm vesh A Cloud support engineer
here at the AWS office in Sydney today
I'm going to show you how you can find
the resources that are associated with
an Amazon ec2 Security Group let's get
started sign into the AWS Management
console and then navigate to the ec2
console in the navigation page choose
security groups that then copy the ID of
the security group whose resources you
want to find next in the navigation pane
choose network interfaces in the search
field enter the security group ID the
search results list all the network
interfaces that are associated with the
security group check the description
column for the network interface to
identify the service or the resource
that is associated with the network
interface if you are using Amazon VPC
latus then you can't use this procedure
to identify the security groups that the
VPC lus network service uses for VPC
Association to check the security groups
that are used with VPC Association use
VPC ltis console or
API you can also run the describ network
interfaces AWS CLI command to find the
network interfaces that are associated
with a specific Security Group if the
output contains network interfaces then
run the described network interface aw
CLI Comm man to find more information
about the resources associated with the
security group so now you know how to
find the resources that are associated
with a specific Security
Group thanks for watching and happy
cloud computing from all of us here at
AWS
